Ask HN: How should a software engineer bring to reality a hardware project idea?
text:
I am a software engineer but have very limited knowledge of hardware. But I have a product idea to both reduce electronic waste and provide good enough system security for the user's data.

The product is a hardware device similar to USB. But I don't know if the idea is even feasible. How does a software engineer, with no knowledge of hardware, bring to life his/her dream. Where should I start? Who should I talk to for guidance and help?

Anyone interested in helping me?

Ask HN: How do I scrape my tweets without using Twitter's own tool?
text:
Given the state of the Twitter workforce I suspect my request for data wouldn't be fulfilled anytime soon. Yet, there must be a way to scrape my tweet history just using the APIs.
Does anyone know of any good (and ideally free) online service I can use for this?

Can Prisma and Hasura be used togetther?
text:
Is it possible to use these technologies above together?

We are currently creating a new service that uses Prisma to communicate with the DB but we have other services built around hasura. Any other service that would need to query the DB in this new Prisma-enabled service would have to do so through a Hasura wrapper.

We need to determine if this is possible.
